name: Michele Rosewoman
description: '''Michele Rosewoman''' (born March 19, 1953) is an American [[jazz]] pianist who leads the big band New Yor-Uba. She has worked with  [[Baikida Carroll]], [[Julius Hemphill]], [[Julian Priester]], [[Oliver Lake]], [[Billy Bang]], [[Freddie Waits]], [[Rufus Reid]], [[Billy Hart]], [[Reggie Workman]], [[Celia Cruz]], [[Alfredo "Chocolate" Armenteros|Chocolate Armenteros]], and [[Paquito D'Rivera]].
